function clean_column(col)
    return lowercasestripwhitespace(replace(split(col, " "), " ", "_"), "-", "_")))
end
```
This function `clean_column` uses various string manipulation functions in Julia to achieve the desired cleaning. It first converts the string to lowercase, strips whitespaces, replaces spaces with underscores, and finally removes hyphens before replacing them with underscores.
